\f1\b0 (a) Executive agencies are required to share relevant supply chain risk information with the FASC if the executive agency has determined there is a reasonable basis to conclude a substantial supply chain risk associated with a source or covered article exists (see \cf3 41 CFR 201\'961.201\cf4 ).\
