\fs24 Subpart 12.2 - Special Requirements for the Acquisition of Commercial Products and Commercial Services\

\f1\b0\fs20 This subpart identifies special requirements for the acquisition of commercial products and commercial services intended to more closely resemble those customarily used in the commercial marketplace, as well as other considerations necessary for proper planning, solicitation, evaluation, and award of contracts for commercial products and commercial services.\

\f0\b 12.202 Market research and description of agency need.\

\f1\b0 (a) Market research (see \cf3 10.001\cf4 ) is an essential element of building an effective strategy for the acquisition of commercial products and commercial services and establishes the foundation for the agency description of need (see \cf3 part 11\cf4 ), the solicitation, and resulting contract.\
(b) The description of agency need must contain sufficient detail for potential offerors of commercial products or commercial services to know which commercial products or commercial services may be suitable. Generally, for acquisitions in excess of the simplified acquisition threshold, an agency\'92s statement of need for a commercial product or commercial service will describe the type of commercial product or commercial service to be acquired and explain how the agency intends to use the product or service in terms of function to be performed, performance requirement or essential physical characteristics. Describing the agency\'92s needs in these terms allows offerors to propose methods that will best meet the needs of the Government.\
(c) Follow the procedures in \cf3 subpart 11.2 \cf4 regarding the identification and availability of specifications, standards and commercial item descriptions.\
(d) Requirements documents shall identify the applicable information and communication technology accessibility standards at 36 CFR 1194.1 (see \cf3 11.002\cf4 (f) and \cf3 subpart 39.2\cf4 ).\
(e) When acquiring information technology using Internet Protocol, agencies must include the appropriate Internet Protocol compliance requirements in accordance with \cf3 11.002\cf4 (g).\

\f0\b 12.203 Procedures for solicitation, evaluation, and award.\

\f1\b0 (a) Contracting officers shall use the policies unique to the acquisition of commercial products and commercial services prescribed in this part in conjunction with the policies and procedures for solicitation, evaluation and award prescribed in \cf3 part 13\cf4 , Simplified Acquisition Procedures; \cf3 part 14 \cf4 Sealed Bidding; or \cf3 part 15\cf4 , Contracting by Negotiation, as appropriate for the particular acquisition. The contracting officer may use the streamlined procedure for soliciting offers for commercial product or commercial service prescribed in \cf3 12.603\cf4 . For acquisitions of commercial products or commercial services exceeding the simplified acquisition threshold but not exceeding $7.5 million ($15 million for acquisitions as described in \cf3 13.500 \cf4 (c)), including options, contracting activities may use any of the simplified procedures authorized by \cf3 subpart 13.5\cf4 .\
(b) Contracting officers shall ensure the criteria at \cf3 15.101-2\cf4 (c) are met when using the lowest price technically acceptable source selection process.\

\f0\b 12.204 Solicitation/contract form.\

\f1\b0 (a) (1) The contracting officer shall use the \cf3 Standard Form 1449\cf4 , Solicitation/Contract/Order for Commercial Products and Commercial Services, if\'97\
(i) The acquisition is expected to exceed the simplified acquisition threshold; (ii) A paper solicitation or contract is being issued; and\
(iii) Procedures at \cf3 12.603 \cf4 are not being used.\
(2) Use of the \cf3 SF 1449 \cf4 is nonmandatory but encouraged for commercial acquisitions not exceeding the simplified acquisition threshold.\
