\fs24 Subpart 19.13 - Historically Underutilized Business Zone (HUBZone) Program\

\fs20 19.1301 General.\

\f1\b0 (a) The Historically Underutilized Business Zone (HUBZone) Act of 1997 (\cf3 15 U.S.C.631 \cf4 note) created the HUBZone Program.\
(b) The purpose of the HUBZone Program is to provide Federal contracting assistance for qualified small business concerns located in historically underutilized business zones, in an effort to increase employment opportunities, investment, and economic development in those areas.\

\f0\b 19.1302 [Reserved].\
19.1303 Status as a HUBZone small business concern.\

\f1\b0 (a) Status as a HUBZone small business concern is determined by the Small Business Administration (SBA) in accordance with 13 CFR Part 126.\
(b) If SBA determines that a concern is a HUBZone small business, it will designate the concern as a HUBZone small business in the Dynamic Small Business Search (DSBS) at 
