\f1\i0 SBA's designation also appears in SAM. Only firms designated in DSBS and SAM as HUBZone small business concerns are eligible for HUBZone preferences. HUBZone preferences are not contingent on the place of performance.\
(c) A joint venture may be considered a HUBZone small business concern if\'97\
(1) The joint venture qualifies as small under \cf3 19.301-1\cf4 (a)(2)(i);\
(2) At least one party to the joint venture is a HUBZone small business concern; and (3) The joint venture complies with \cf3 13 CFR 126.616(a) \cf4 through \cf3 (c)\cf4 .\
(d) To be eligible for a HUBZone contract under this section, a HUBZone small business concern must be a HUBZone small business concern at the time of its initial offer.\

