(i) If If the new determination for the primary site of the work changes any wage rates for classifications to be used in the contract, the contracting officer may cancel the solicitation only in accordance with \cf3 14.404-1\cf4 . Otherwise the contracting officer shall award the contract and incorporate the new determination to be effective on the date of contract award. The contracting officer shall equitably adjust the contract price for any increased or decreased cost of performance resulting from any changed wage rates.\
(ii) If the new determination for the primary site of the work does not change any wage rates, the contracting officer shall award the contract and modify it to include the number and date of the new determination. (See \cf3 43.103\cf4 (b)(1).)\
(c) The following procedure applies when contracting by negotiation:\
(1) If a project wage determination will or does expire before contract award, the contracting officer shall request a\
