\fs24 Subpart 22.8 - Equal Employment Opportunity\

\f1\b0\fs20 This subpart prescribes policies and procedures pertaining to nondiscrimination in employment by contractors and subcontractors.\

\f0\b 22.801 Definitions.\

\f1\b0 As used in this subpart-\

\f2\i Affirmative action program 
\f1\i0 means a contractor\'92s program that complies with Department of Labor regulations to ensure equal opportunity in employment to minorities and women.\

\f2\i Compliance evaluation 
\f1\i0 means any one or combination of actions that the Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs (OFCCP) may take to examine a Federal contractor\'92s compliance with one or more of the requirements of E.O.11246.\

\f2\i Contractor 
\f1\i0 includes the terms "prime contractor" and "subcontractor."\

\f2\i Deputy Assistant Secretary 
\f1\i0 means the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Federal Contract Compliance, U.S. Department of Labor, or a designee.\

\f2\i Equal Opportunity clause 
\f1\i0 means the clause at \cf3 52.222-26\cf4 , Equal Opportunity, as prescribed in \cf3 22.810\cf4 (e).\

\f2\i E.O.11246 
\f1\i0 means PartsII and IV of Executive Order11246, September 24,1965 (30 FR12319), and any Executive order amending or superseding this order (see \cf3 22.802\cf4 ). This term specifically includes the Equal Opportunity clause at \cf3 52.222-26\cf4 , and the rules, regulations, and orders issued pursuant to E.O.11246 by the Secretary of Labor or a designee.\

\f2\i Gender identity 
\f1\i0 has the meaning given by the Department of Labor\'92s Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs, and is found at \cf3 www.dol.gov/ofccp/LGBT/LGBT_FAQs.html\cf4 .\

\f2\i Prime contractor 
\f1\i0 means any person who holds, or has held, a Government contract subject to E.O.11246.\

\f2\i Recruiting and training agency 
\f1\i0 means any person who refers workers to any contractor or provides or supervises apprenticeship or training for employment by any contractor.\

\f2\i Sexual orientation 
\f1\i0 has the meaning given by the Department of Labor\'92s Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs, and is found at \cf3 www.dol.gov/ofccp/LGBT/LGBT_FAQs.html\cf4 .\

\f2\i Site of construction 
\f1\i0 means the general physical location of any building, highway, or other change or improvement to real property that is undergoing construction, rehabilitation, alteration, conversion, extension, demolition, or repair; and any temporary location or facility at which a contractor or other participating party meets a demand or performs a function relating to a Government contract or subcontract.\

\f2\i Subcontract 
\f1\i0 means any agreement or arrangement between a contractor and any person (in which the parties do not stand in the relationship of an employer and an employee)-\
(1) For the purchase, sale, or use of personal property or nonpersonal services that, in whole or in part, are necessary to the performance of any one or more contracts; or\
