(2) Administer contract financing so as to aid, not impede, the acquisition;\
(3) Avoid any undue risk of monetary loss to the Government through the financing;\
(4) Include the form of contract financing deemed to be in the Government\'92s best interest in the solicitation (see \cf3 32.106\
\cf4 and \cf3 32.113\cf4 ); and\
(5) Monitor the contractor\'92s use of the contract financing provided and the contractor\'92s financial status.\
(b) If the contractor is a small business concern, the contracting officer must give special attention to meeting the contractor\'92s contract financing need. However, a contractor\'92s receipt of a certificate of competency from the Small Business Administration has no bearing on the contractor\'92s need for or entitlement to contract financing.\
(c) Subject to specific agency regulations and paragraph (d) of this section, the contracting officer- (1) May provide customary contract financing in accordance with \cf3 32.113\cf4 ; and\
(2) Must not provide unusual contract financing except as authorized in \cf3 32.114\cf4 .\
